                  <li>‚úÖ Better protection against ear infections</li>
                  <li>‚ö†Ô∏è More likely to get stuck and cause blockages</li>
                  <li>‚ö†Ô∏è Hearing aids can push it deeper</li>
                  <li>‚ö†Ô∏è May need professional cleaning more often</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="patient-insight">
                  <p><strong>Real talk:</strong> If you have sticky wax and you're reading this, you probably need professional help. Home methods rarely work well for this type.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="wax-type flaky-type">
              <div class="type-header">
                <h3>Flaky Type (Less Common)</h3>
                <div class="type-badge uncommon">5% of people</div>
              </div>
              <div class="type-content">
                <h4>What it looks like:</h4>
                <p>Grey to white, dry and flaky</p>

                <h4>What this means for you:</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>‚úÖ Less likely to cause blockages</li>
                  <li>‚úÖ Usually clears naturally</li>
