            <div class="process-step">
              <div class="step-number">1</div>
              <div class="step-content">
                <h4>Your Ears Make Fresh Wax Daily</h4>
                <p>Like a factory that never stops, your ears constantly produce new wax to replace old wax. Most people never notice this happening.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="process-step">
              <div class="step-number">2</div>
              <div class="step-content">
                <h4>Jaw Movement Slowly Pushes Old Wax Out</h4>
                <p>Every time you talk, chew, or yawn, your jaw movement creates tiny vibrations that gradually move old wax toward your outer ear. This takes about 2-4 weeks.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="process-step">
              <div class="step-number">3</div>
              <div class="step-content">
                <h4>Old Wax Falls Out Naturally</h4>
                <p>When wax reaches your outer ear, it dries up and flakes off during normal activities like showering or washing your face. You might never even see it.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="process-step">
              <div class="step-number">4</div>
              <div class="step-content">
                <h4>The Cycle Repeats Forever</h4>
                <p>This process should continue automatically for your entire life, keeping your ears clean and protected without any effort from you.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="when-it-breaks">
