                    <h5>Genetics</h5>
                    <p>Some people just produce more wax or have narrower ear canals</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="reason-item">
                    <h5>Age</h5>
                    <p>As you get older, wax becomes drier and harder to move naturally</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="reason-item">
                    <h5>Ear Canal Shape</h5>
                    <p>Some people have curves or narrow spots that trap wax</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="reason-category">
                <h4>üéØ Things That Happen in Modern Life</h4>
                <div class="reason-list">
                  <div class="reason-item">
                    <h5>Earbuds and Headphones</h5>
                    <p>Regular use pushes wax deeper and blocks natural migration</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="reason-item">
                    <h5>Hearing Aids</h5>
                    <p>Act like a cork, preventing wax from moving outward</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="reason-item">
                    <h5>Dusty Environments</h5>
                    <p>Your ears produce extra wax to protect against dust and debris</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="reason-category">
                <h4>‚ùå Things People Do That Make It Worse</h4>
                <div class="reason-list">
                  <div class="reason-item">
                    <h5>Cotton Bud Use</h5>
                    <p>Pushes wax deeper and compacts it against your eardrum</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="reason-item">
                    <h5>Finger Cleaning</h5>
                    <p>Introduces bacteria and pushes wax deeper into the canal</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="reason-item">
                    <h5>Aggressive Washing</h5>
                    <p>Irritates the ear canal and can push water and soap deeper</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Cotton Bud Truth Section -->
    <section class="cotton-bud-section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="section-title">The Uncomfortable Truth About Cotton Buds</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">We need to talk about this honestly. Most people use cotton buds, and most people have been told they shouldn't. Here's the real story:</p>

        <div class="cotton-bud-reality">
